%matplotlib inline
import pandas as pd 
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn import preprocessing
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

np.random.seed(47)

df = pd.read_csv('https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/'
        'machine-learning-databases/abalone/abalone.data', usecols=(0,1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8), header=None)

df.columns = ['Sex', 'Length', 'Diameter', 'Height', 'Whole weight', 'Shucked weight', 'Viscera weight', 'Shell weight', 'Rings']

selected_columns = df[['Sex']]
new_df = selected_columns.copy()
new_df = new_df.iloc[:300]
colors = np.where(new_df['Sex']=="M",'r','-')
colors[new_df['Sex']=="F"] = 'g'
colors[new_df['Sex']=="I"] = 'b'
print(colors)

X = np.array(df['Length']).reshape(-1,1)
y = np.array(df['Rings'])

print(df.head(15))

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.5, random_state=50)
print(y.shape,X_train.shape, X_test.shape, y_train.shape, y_test.shape)

# Length linear regression plot
In [83]:
from matplotlib.collections import LineCollection

X = np.array(df['Length']).reshape(-1,1)
y = np.array(df['Rings'])

%time regr = LinearRegression().fit(X_train,y_train)

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.5, random_state=50)

y_predicted = regr.predict(X_test)
N = len(y_train)

segments = [[[X_train[i], y_train[i]], [X_train[i], y_predicted[i]]] for i in range(N)]

lc = LineCollection(segments, zorder=0)
lc.set_array(np.ones(len(y_train)))
lc.set_alpha(0.5)
lc.set_linewidths(0.5 * np.ones(len(y_train)))

fig = plt.figure(figsize=[24,10])
# plot the training data
plt.plot(X_train, y_train, 'r.', markersize=12)
# plot the prediction line
x_lin = np.linspace(0,320,1000).reshape(-1,1)
plt.plot(x_lin, regr.predict(x_lin), color='blue',linewidth=3,alpha=0.5)
# plot the redisuals
plt.gca().add_collection(lc)

plt.xlim([0,.8])
plt.ylim([0,30])
plt.xlabel('Length')
plt.ylabel('Rings')
plt.legend(('Data', 'Regression Fit'), loc='lower right')
plt.title('Linear regression')

# plot the regression line
plt.show()

CPU times: user 1.16 ms, sys: 201 µs, total: 1.36 ms
Wall time: 1.17 ms

y1 = np.array(df['Rings'])

    X1, y1, test_size=0.5, random_state=50)

                  ('linear', LinearRegression(fit_intercept=True))])
